          <p><strong>The risk an investor is actually taking.</strong> The concept is validated (technically feasible, per the development team). The market is proven (massive, growing, structurally underserved). The design partner context is real. The primary risk is execution speed — whether Interphase can establish category leadership and client relationships before a well-resourced player attempts to retrofit cultural infrastructure onto an existing HR platform. The antidote is depth: the Chaperone network, the biological framing, and the multi-lens architecture are not things that can be copy-pasted. They require a distinctive philosophical foundation that takes years to build credibly.</p>
